            <debateSection name="amendments" id="sub1">
                <heading>Amendments</heading>
            </debateSection>
            <debateSection id="sec1" name="section">
                <p>Under<ref id="ref1" href="/ak/bill/234/main#sec5">SECTION FIVE</ref>, Government introduced an
                    amendment which seeks to take into account all sectors of activities covered by the reevaluation of
                    the nature of investments giving rise to exemption from taxation of capital gains tax, referring the
                    modalities for application of this provision to the regulatory instrument.
                </p>
                <p>This amendment was accepted by your Committee and
                    <ref href="/ak/bill/234/main#sec5-subsec7" id="ref2">SECTION FIVE (7)</ref>
                    is reformulated as follows:
                    <mod id="mod1">
                        <ref href="/ak/bill/234/main#sec5-subsec7" id="ref3">SECTION FIVE:</ref>
                        “
                        <quotedStructure id="qtd1">
                            <subsection id="sec5-subsec7">
                                <content>
                                    <p>
                                        <mmod id="mod1-mmod1">
                                            <ref href="/ak/bill/345/main#sec10" id="ref4">Section Ten</ref>
                                            of the Finance Law of the 2010 financial year is hereby amended and
                                            supplemented as follows:

                                            <mod id="mod1-mmod1-mod1">
                                                <quotedText id="qtd2">1) A legal system for the revaluation of tangible
                                                    and intangible depreciable and non-depreciable fixed assets is
                                                    hereby instituted.
                                                </quotedText>
                                            </mod>
                                            <omissis>…………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………
                                            </omissis>
                                            <mod id="mod1-mmod1-mod3">
                                                <quotedText id="qtd3">4) Revaluation shall be carried out no later than
                                                    31 December 2013.
                                                </quotedText>
                                            </mod>
                                            <omissis>…………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………
                                                ……
                                            </omissis>
                                            <mod id="mod1-mmod1-mod4">
                                                <quotedText id="qtd4">6) The revaluation surplus shall be subject to a
                                                    5% levy in discharge from
                                                    any other tax, duty, levy and royalty.
                                                </quotedText>
                                            </mod>
                                            <mod id="mod1-mmod1-mod5">
                                                <quotedText id="qtd5">7) However, the above 5% levy in discharge shall
                                                    not be applicable in the case of reinvestment of the revaluation
                                                    surplus within two fiscal years ended, in accordance with the forms
                                                    and conditions specified in Sections 105 et seq of the General Tax
                                                    Code by regulation.
                                                </quotedText>
                                            </mod>
                                            ”
                                        </mmod>
                                    </p>
                                </content>
                            </subsection>
                        </quotedStructure>
                    </mod>
                </p>
                <scene>SECTION FIVE was adopted after this amendment.</scene>
